RaMS Lab @ UCR

 

Welcome to the Robotics and Medical Systems (RaMS) Laboratory

 

Located in the Department of Mechanical Engineering at University of California Riverside, the RaMS lab focuses on soft and compliant robots to address fundamental challenges in a variety of medical and agricultural applications, such as minimally invasive surgery, cancer detection, drug delivery, rehabilitation, and harvesting. Specifically, our research is targeted towards:

  • Imaging-Guided Surgical Robots
  • Fluidic Soft Robots
  • Tendon-Driven Robots
  • Smart Material Robots
  • Medical Devices

Receiving the NSF SCH Award for Robotics for Tissue Disease Diagnosis!

by Jun Sheng | Aug 16, 2024

We're thrilled to announce that we've been awarded the National Science Foundation (NSF) Smart Health and Biomedical Research in the Era of Artificial Intelligence and Advanced Data Science award for Comprehensive Tissue Disease Diagnosis Using a Multimodal Robotic System. This is a 4-year collaborative project across UCR (Co-PIs Dr. Chen Li and Dr. Salman Asif), UCSD (PI Dr. Sheng Xu), and City of Hope (PI Dr. Mustafa Raoof).

Welcome Mariam Mikhail, Annabelle Yang, and Steven Vu to join RAMS for summer research. They are supported by the UCR Mentoring Summer Research Internship Program (MSRIP). They are working on surgical robotics and agricultural robotics projects!

Receiving the NSF CAREER Award for Microfabricated Mesoscale Soft Robots!

by Jun Sheng | May 9, 2024

We're thrilled to announce that we've been awarded the prestigious National Science Foundation (NSF) CAREER award for our groundbreaking work on Microfabricated Mesoscale Soft Robots with Embodied Intelligence for Minimally Invasive Surgery. This grant extends over five years, from 2024 to 2029, empowering us to pioneer new frontiers in medical robotics and intelligent systems.
